3.11	Piet_Cronje	Piet Cronjé	Pieter Arnoldus Cronjé, commonly known as Piet Cronjé (English pronunciation: kron-YAIR; Colesberg, Cape Colony, 4 October 1836 – Potchefstroom, Transvaal, 4 February 1911) was a general of the South African Republic's military forces during the Anglo-Boer wars of 1880-1881 and 1899-1902.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/3a/PACronje_CHM_VA2863.jpg/225px-PACronje_CHM_VA2863.jpg
